I went there by 11pm, the bartender was so rude to all of us, usually staff are amazing but this one is so rude
Great cocktails but it is a bit stuffy.  residents and graduate students like to spend time here.
Love the food and cocktails.  The ambiance/lighting is also amazing!  Love this place!
It was really good. Tuesday was $1oyster night...it may only be for lent...happy surprise ❣

I’ve been here a few times and always loved the food, so I decided to celebrate my birthday here with seven friends. I made the reservation over a week in advance so I assumed the restaurant would be prepared for a party of this size on a Tuesday evening. The dining room was busy so I understand a little bit of a delay in some things, and our drinks and appetizers sure took awhile. However, our food came out in shifts. Two guests were served, then five minutes later the next three, and the last three (myself included) waited over fifteen minutes for our entrées to come out. In that time, our server stopped by and briefly apologized, and another woman who I’m assuming was the manager came by. I was relieved and hoping for an explanation, instead she said “sorry about that, there’s a lot of people in the dining area tonight.” She didn’t offer anyway to make it up to us, or any real excuse, instead she simply dismissed us. By the time we got our meals, nearly everyone at our table was finished with theirs. This rating is one star because no matter how amazing the food and cocktails were, nothing can make up for how awful that service was. Gratuity was included due to my party’s size, but everyone at my table was unhappy about how much they had to tip for such terrible service.

The food was phenomenal and the atmosphere was wonderful (an old fashioned feel). We ordered cheese curds, a salad, fish and chips, a burger, and finished with cheesecake. All items were absolutely delicious. They should definitely expect me back!
Fun date night location!
Great food, great drinks, great atmosphere.

I appreciate a great strip, however I was disappointed with the service. The two ladies that I saw “working” when I visited continuously ignored their guests; it was obvious they could care less about their work ethic. I received a snarky comment from one of the female servers when I asked about the cocktails available for the night. Maybe I’ll try again, the food and cocktail that I had was great, but I pray that neither of these girls is my server.
This is a great place to have a casual business meeting or, relax after a long crazy day at the University.
The happy hour drinks are awesome! Worth it to be your pre-dinner spot. Or just your dinner spot!

I've been there twice and the bartenders were super rude condescending snobs. If it just happened once, I would say the bartender was having a bad day. When it happened twice, I figured it's their business motto. When I asked for one of the drinks on their menu, they said said they didn't have one of the liquors needed for the drink. When I asked for them to substitute that liquor, they snarkily said come back in three days so they could infuse pineapple into it.  Is it not possible to just add a splash of pineapple juice?  When my husband asked what whiskeys were available for the old fashioned, he was told there were 75 whiskeys and he couldn't name them all. Couldn't he have just given us a whiskey menu? If I could give zero stars I would. I will never go back.
Delicious food. Yummy cocktails. Great atmosphere.
Love the selection and atmosphere
Good food, great cocktails.
First time there and food was excellent as well as our waiter.  Need more light, did not like using our phones to read menus or see the food that was prepared so nicely.
Very nice dinning experience. Everything was outstanding.
Favorite cocktail bar in Iowa City; solid happy hour & free pool table and darts
Great place, nice beer selection.

Wow. Fancy spot. I attended an event on the 3rd floor and the space was gorgeous. The bar is just as hip and cool as any place I've been to in Chicago. But the cocktails aren't $18 each because we are in the blessed state of Iowa. I loved the ambiance of this place. The drinks were great. The food was good, but I didn't eat much. This would be a great date night location or a place to host an upscale party.
Poor bartending...

Can't say enough positive things about this place. Excellent service, incredible cocktails, wonderful food, and an environment that would rival any restaurant in the corridor. If you're looking for a top tier experience in IC, Clinton Street should be at the top of your list.

Unique, quiet, low key place with tasty selections of creative food options. Large selection of drinks as well. Staff is attentive and helpful. Pleasantly surprised with flavors. Nicely done. Strongly recommend.
The food is fantastic. It's a nice intimate setting for dinning. The billiard room is a nice touch.

Drinks here is a great time. Nice to play cards at the tables if you bring your own. The atmosphere is of the highest quality in IC. I've visited the Clinton Street Social Club quite a few times with my girlfriend and some friends here and there, but increasingly recently the table side service has been just worse and worse. It used to be MAX 10 minutes your waiter would stop by your table, but this past week when some friends and I came, it took almost half an hour for our group to get the checks and pay the bill.  Honestly I would tell anyone that the Clinton Social Club is a 5/5 out my mouth. I would say to avoid certain timeslots where the bar will be too full for you and who you come with that we definitely haven't mastered yet.

My husband and I came into the city for the IA game and found this gem! Enjoyed the drinks, conversation and Justin (mixologist) so much we returned the next night! Can't wait for our next trip! So many creative drinks and the atmosphere was just what we were looking for. Thanks for the great service Justin, happy birthday!
My favorite spot in Iowa City. Excellent food and cocktails!

CSSC is always such a pleasure to go to. Amazing cocktails, one of the best whiskey collections in Iowa, and an incredible food menu that rotates seasonally. And let's not forget the service and atmosphere that makes you never want to leave. The salmon last night was to die for, and a special request for a "legit mocktail" was wonderfully met.
Tasty drinks, knowledgeable and talented bartender
Other than being a bit noisy, it's a great Club!
I've always experienced good service, food, and atmosphere. Decent place for a chill night.
Best cocktail bar in Eastern Iowa, easily.

Visited this fine establishment for a drink while out for a friends birthday. The drinks are in my opinion the best in iowa city. They can be pricey but are made correctly and with quality ingredients. I'm a gin drinker and had a French 75. It was fantastic! I would say it is a hidden gem in Iowa City.

This place was absolutely awesome. They have a full cocktail menu and plenty of spirits for you to choose from. They have fresh oysters that are just out of this world, would highly recommend. Staff is dressed to the 9s and they are welcoming and very friendly. Highly recommend making a stop here
Maybe the best restaurant in Iowa City.
Delicious and very unique drinks.

Here on business Food was tasty, portions were just right, but the star was my Pisco Sour!i ate at the bar. My drink was perfectly made & the presentation was as it should be. Cheers to the bartender/server Devon.

Clinton Street was great. I've been wanting to come visit for years now after stumbling across it looking for good cocktail spots in the state. The staff and management were all phenomenal people. I can't say enough good things about them. The cocktails were stellar. We started with the oysters and some house cocktails off the menu that were all exceptionally done. Later, the bartenders and staff brought out a few different individually customized cocktails for us to try and they were all impressive and spot on. The burger was exceptional. Salmon cakes were solid. All in all I really loved my visit and glad I was able to make it happen. I am very grateful for my experience and they way were treated by everyone at Clinton Street. Highly recommended if you're looking for a laid back atmosphere with first rate cocktails, great food, and even better people to be around. Thank you and best of luck to you all!
Very good— I ordered the fish and chips.
Best happy hour in town.

I've been here a couple times before, but never had a chance to try their food. Fantastic. Appetizer of hush puppies came with a wonderful dipping sauce, and my entree of fish and chips (with the option of malt vinegar as a dressing, which is a must) was incredible. And as always, drinks second to none. Murderer's Row is always a nice way to get acquainted with some less common or pricey whiskeys you won't find most places, and Wednesdays they play a healthy dose of Tom Waits. I've never felt out if place here, dressed up or dressed down. What's not to love!
Okay
Great staff, amazing drinks looking forward to trying the food sometime soon.
Great food! Jazz every other thursday.
Quite a variety of cocktails and whiskey with a limited beer and wine menu
Cool place to hang out
Great atmosphere for a drink with family or friends
They have a serious fly problem. Flies were harassing me nonstop...
Bartender said no when I asked him to make a Gin and Tonic in a different way. Also, the tonic water was not carbonated. Liked the popcorn though.
Great drinks and neat atmosphere!!
Best Cocktail Bar in town.  I recommend Dan as your mixer.  Fantastic mixer; as well as a Fantastic looker.
I'll probably never be back in Iowa city to go back but I'm still glad I went when I was there! Its cozy and tucked away and the food is amazing!
Hands down the best cocktails in Iowa City and the surrounding area. This is a great laid back place with some sophistication. Great food as well, especially the poutine!
Fantastic cheese curds and only place in town with good hush puppies. Original and creative drink menu. Great atmosphere.

It’s hard to believe a place like this exists in Iowa City. The bartenders are superbly creative and knowledgeable. Whether you’d like a recommendation for a whiskey straight up or a suggestion for a cocktail that fits your style, they’re on point every time. Great atmosphere and a cozy feel. Much recommend. Very class.

The ambiance was nice and happy hour was not full of rough boistrous college students. The waittress was not extremely attentive, sort of just there at sporadic moments. The Hotel Palomar is a must try!
Love me some CSS.
Great ambience, very good food and wait staff.
This has been a favorite of mine since I have moved to Iowa. Great atmosphere, and unique cocktails. High dining cuisine at a reasonable price. Highly recommended.
Yummy. Everything cooked just right, and the ingredients were all fresh.
Awesome bar! Top shelf quality bar service. Great staff! Excellent food.
Excellent Food.  Really fun party space.  Very nice bartenders.

This place is amazing, the owner is a great guy, and the staff answers any and every question, I love the fact they do industry night too! The drinks here are so unique and interesting and so is the food. This place never fails me!
Really nice atmosphere, really good menu, and I loved the cocktails. .
Hands down my favorite place in Iowa city! Grab a classic cocktail and try the fresh oysters 👌🏻

LOVE Clinton Street Social Club. The drinks are sophisticated and not to sweet. The Cheese Curds are fantastic. We do here 1-2 times a month when we can get away from the kids and really love the atmosphere. At the bar we usually either chat with the bartender or there's always someone really interesting from the University that is hanging out.
Good spot to bring visiting guests. Lovely atmosphere, feels like I’m in the show Peaky Blinders
Taste and great for happy hour!
Hip and young - without the pretensions. Great atmosphere and classical interiors w/ great cocktails. A must when in IC.
Its no one eyed jakes, but it has a swanky vibe with mustached bar tenders. Pretty cool spot for downtown Iowa City but definitely pricey.
Good drinks, decent food, and a nice atmosphere. A good place for a small group to gather. You can reserve the top floor for small parties as well.
Nice fancy place in the middle of the fields
My favorite place for good drinks and a relaxing environment. Unique cocktails and excellent food...try the oysters, best around!
Great atmosphere, drinks, and food!
Wonderful attention to detail.  Comfortable, quaint setting.  Interesting varied drink menu, and a nice happy hour.
My favorite place downtown. Very classy atmosphere, and great menu.

I usually love this place, but I went there two/three weeks ago and the service was pretty poor. The hostess was rude from the start and I felt that because we wanted to sit in the billiards room that our patronage was not appreciated. No one explained that we wouldn’t have a waiter, the bar was full of customers, and I felt like I wasn’t wanted there. I was there to spend money and have a good time but was treated poorly by all the staff I met that day. I want to go back with friends, but I also want to be able to enjoy my time there.
Drinks are great, and the place has a very unique atmosphere. The presentation is just as good as the food. Can never go wrong with the oysters or the charcuterie board!
Great food and service. Atmosphere was fun and enjoyed the live music.
Nice beers,excellent fries,right kind of mood
Ian is the best bartender
A lot of stairs for older people. Food was fantastic. We were there for a work function and had the whole third floor. Very nice time and great atmosphere.
This place has only gotten better over time. The kitchen staff is doing everything right
Stopped in for dinner and had a really nice but, overpriced, chicken sandwich and had a local hard cider on tap.

This place has the coolest vibe! It has that socialite, speakeasy feel. I made my husband bring me here because I had heard such great things. He also owed me as he was going to be out of town for our 1 year wedding anniversary. Neither of us are big cocktail drinkers so we opted for beer. It was cool to see they had a beer on the menu that is especially made for their establishment from a local brewery in the area. I ordered the BBLT which totally delivered on the promise of bacon by including it in the name twice. My husband got the macaroni and cheese which was amazing! They should have used the word cheese twice because it totally met in the cheese department. We will totally be back although next time we will make a point to get there for happy hour because they have great happy hour food and drink specials.
Amazing bourbon collection and crafted cocktails. Love the atmosphere!
Wonderful as usual
Always enjoy my visits. Enjoy the atmosphere and thier cocktails. One of my favorites items (not in the menu) is thier bucket of bacon.

The food is decent here—we tried the cheese fondue to start, which was really tasty and good consistency. For dinner we got the chicken, which was juicy and in a good sauce, and the BLT sandwich. The prices are a little high, but still pairs well with their good cocktails. I had the Annabel Lee, which was refreshing. The service was slow to start since we waited a while to get our order in, but was redeemed the rest of the night. We were given more bread for the fondue without asking, and the server cared about how we liked the food. Good place for a date night once in a while!
Nice place

Hard to find from the street, but very cool spot. Check the concert lineup before you go to know if you need a reservation. And get one of those weird mixology drinks. Treat yourself to a drink with an egg white in it.
Love this place. It’s my go-to amazing cocktails and their food never disappoints.

Overall a 3.5. I decided to round up for it because I think the drink menu is pretty solid for those into cocktails and the door menu is attempting to be as progressive. For my few days in town this was the most gastro style place around.  Service at bar was beyond horrible.  Had the crab pot - meh. Cool idea but lacking flavor.  Hanger steak - This was very good. Cooked perfectly, tender, flavorful and served with good accompaniments. Large piece of meat for a hanger.  Beignets - a twist on the classic. The flavor was decently close but not quite the same. Still it’s enough to bring back those warm memories.  Worth going: yea, I think so. Certainly more expensive than most places in the area but most progressive menu and good drinks. Environment was trendy and is a welcomed change from the college scene surrounding it.
Great place to meet up with friends for drinks. They have a great selection of beers on tap as well as wines and spirits.
Great atmosphere and fun bartenders!
Friendly bartender. Tasty curds. Good old fashioned.
Good food, friendly staff and great drinks.
Devilled eggs are great but aren't really devilled eggs. No need to reinvent the egg wheel.
Best cocktail spot in Iowa City
Great food and drinks! Expensive
Food was good.  Sevice was good.  Really expensive
The food and service were very good, but the metal chairs were really uncomfortable.
Beautiful building! Great food and great service.
Fantastic food. Great deals for happy hour (4-6pm M-F). Had the pork loin and it was amazing. It was on the higher side for price but they also have cheaper options as well.
Their charcuterie tray is amazing the steak was done perfectly
Great atmosphere and very well made drinks.
Stairs
My favorite place in iowa city...southern mules w a great selection of bourbons...all cocktails are great
Great food and atmosphere...drink service a bit slow but had a great time with awesome friends:)

This is a fun spot to eat and drink. It's a bit on the pricier side, but if you want a fancy cocktail and some interesting gourmet food, this is a definite place to check out in Iowa City. The drink price range makes this less of an undergrad hangout. They've got pool and darts too and a second floor for events that has its own bar, very nice.

The food is very good, however the portions seem a bit small for the price. The overall aesthetic of the place is cool. When we went it was very cold (apparently the thermostat malfunctioned or something). It's also really dark at night. Overall, it was a good experience and I would recommend it.
Great drinks and environment. Although slightly pricy, I’ll gladly pay it for the quality I’ve always gotten here.
Seasonal cocktails are excellent. Food was very good, pretty rich. Small food menu and dinning area. Everything was expensive but worth it. I would recommend making a reservation.
The drinks here are amazing. Also expensive, but they are so close to perfection paying $9-12 seems appropriate. Food is also excellent. I always enjoy meals here.
Obviously amazing! Best cocktails in Iowa City!!
Service was excellent.  Beer was good.  Fish and chips were good but portion was on small side.  Creme Brûlée was perfect.  Atmosphere was very comfortable.
The food was good, I enjoyed it. The restaurant had a faint, odd smell when we first came in, but it went away after we'd been there awhile.
The cocktails at Clinton Street Social Club are primo, but the green eggs and ham (deviled eggs) are to die for.
Fun place for drinks and apps with friends. A bit pricey, but great atmosphere that's different than most of downtown. A tad bit on the small side too.
This place is probably too cool for me, but I love the vibe and nowhere else can you get the kind of Martini's they have.
Pricey, but great cocktails.

The food is really good, great mixed drinks and beer selection, and outstanding service. Add that to a cool looking place with a great view, and you have another gem for IC. My only knock is they could expand their food menu by an item or two, but what they do make is superb!

1 star because I was completely ignored by the bar tender. Also was passed over on orders. Came here after work and the staff was just rude with their attitudes. I will be passing on my experience at the hospital where I work to my physician friends for sure.
Great food,  great atmosphere, great service!! Definitely recommend!!
Ask for the 'Blushing Orphan'
Food, cocktails, and waitstaff are always great. Very cool ambiance.
If you're trying to escape the college crowd head here. Great cocktails and atmosphere.
Is the only restaurant in Iowa City that has fresh Oysters, big selection of beer & food is delicious.
Great cocktails!  Knowledgeable bartenders

Great atmosphere, regular jazz every first and third Thursday (will double check). Pricey drinks, but the cocktails are well made and the staff are very professional. Bathrooms always clean and well stocked!
Great cocktails, one of the best, if not the best in Iowa City. Stop in for their specials, or grab a bite to eat. I like their impressive selection of appetisers.

Excellent bar with some of the best food in Iowa City. Belongs on the short list of best places to eat and drink. You can keep it simple or really go all out here. Would also be my first choice if I was looking to host an event.
Best craft cocktails​ in town, but you pay for it
Inviting and relaxing upscale atmosphere suitable for an older crowd located in the middle of campus town. Craft drinks are the specialty here.
Classy bar with attentive and friendly bar tenders.
Great bar. Not loud or hectic. Creative modern drinks, and well made classics. One of the few bars in Iowa City that you're treated well.
Great drinks and food.

Been here 5+ times now - great experience, especially with the drinks and the happy hour food (haven't tried a real meal yet here - not sure if that's their specialty).  Anyways - have come with groups ranging from just one friend to a birthday party with 15 people in the pool table room - and it's been great service, great drinks every time.  Really good quality stuff - and at happy hour you have an awesome deal - especially with half price tap beers (great selection of local craft), and good selection of cocktails.  The fried cheese curds are amazing. Oysters are solid too (and I have lived in the pacific northwest for 15 years before coming to Iowa - so I know).
Almost always empty. High prices. Lots of stairs. Hooligans outside. No rooftop. No back entry. Decor ok. Staff ok. Cocktails ok. Music meh.
Love their cocktail menu!
Great drinks, great atmosphere. A favorite hang out spot.
Nice atmosphere. Jazz first and third Thursday. Good happy hour.
little bit small place for dining but overall it is not bad

Great food, excellent drinks, and an unbeatable atmosphere make this an establishment everyone should try.  The bar staff are incredibly knowledgeable and fun to chat with, and the wait staff know how to provide excellent service without seeming overbearing.
Nice atmosphere, excellent cocktail and drinks.. food was ok.. enjoyed!
Nice drink choices
Great atmosphere, awesome food and excellent service. We will be back!
Bartender was extrodinarely rude. No doubt in my mind he had no desire to have returning customers.
If you go to this bar, please be desperate. If you have another option go there.
My favorite bar/restaurant in Iowa City.  Speakeasy decor, excellent cocktails.  Food is very, very good.  Beware Chicago-level prices.

Sophisticated seasonal menu options that include local ingredients and a wide variety of adult beverages.  I had a taste of several appetizers when I was there including hush puppies, fondue (an amazing mix of sweet and savory, with Gruyere, white wine, rosemary, pear, and caramelized onions,) mussels (tender mussels in a delicious ale and fennel sauce and conveniently served with some baguette to soak up lots of sauce), and a deviled egg (I don't usually like blue cheese, but this egg was very tasty!)  There was a good selection of beer/wine/liquor with eclectic cocktails made with thought and style.  They have a back room with a gorgeous pool table and dart boards.  If you are a 30-something looking to avoid intoxicated undergraduates, this is a great destination.
I always get a great education on brown alcohol when I'm there. Wonderful cocktails

High quality drink selection with a quality food menu as well. It's a great place for conversational drinks on a weekend night, and they feature my favorite cocktails in Iowa City. The only let-down for me has been their poutine, but the rest of the menu has been great.
This place has a great cocktail selection and a very delicious appetizers. Also has a fancy pool table.
Great cocktails!

Friendly staff. Super Clean. Not 21 year olds puking, its a higher class environment and nice to be in. Menu is unique and awesome.  The best oysters in Iowa....that I can find.  Theyre delivered directly from Chicago almost everyday. Get the pear.
Great cocktails. Great food. Decent live music. Old time speakeasy feel.

Before I write anything I just want to say thank you to whoever devised this establishment.  When you enter "The Social Club", and see the dimly-lit stairwell leading up into the bar area, it leads one to believe that there is an experience actually associated with the whole thing. An experience? Not a chance, not in Iowa City! Well, let me tell ya buddy you get one here, and a damn good one too!!! Delicious, creative menu items are coupled with a wonderfully attentive staff. Feast your eyes on the whiskeys that adorn the wall behind the bar! I'm not gonna recommend anything, because you need to try EVERYTHING. Get your lazy a** over here and join the club.
Amazing fare for a gastropub. The Moscow mules were on point and also enjoyed the beef. Iowans is know for its cattle and produced.

Jazz/blues music, classic mix drink selection and retro ambience makes this bar/restaurant a nice change to the standard bar establishments you find downtown. Service is always stellar with appetizers reasonably priced.
Nice place to stay for a drink or two.
Phenomenal service, food, drinks, and atmosphere. If I could change one thing, it would be the volume of the music at moments when I am telling a quiet story. And really, is that a complaint?

Absolutely AWESOME! Mellow jazz and blues at a decibel level allowing conversation...great drinks...unique food offerings...and owner (Brian) and his staff who ALWAYS put the customer first. A taste of The French Quarter...in Iowa City. Go! (You'll be glad you did.)
Great cocktails,  appetizers, food and service.  What's not to love.
